Class InputStreamSource

All Implemented Interfaces:
TokenizerSource
Deprecated. in favour of the new ReaderSource

public class InputStreamSource
extends java.lang.Object
implements TokenizerSource

Implementation of the TokenizerSource interface for Reader sources, e.g. InputStreamReader.

The class can be compared with InputStreamTokenizer, that has approximately the same (own) method set. While the InputStreamTokenizer is a class directly derived from AbstractTokenizer, InputStreamSource is used in conjunction with the PluginTokenizer. That way it is possible to switch from one Reader to another dynamically.

Author:
Heiko Blau
See Also:
Tokenizer, AbstractTokenizer, PluginTokenizer, Reader
